File: Convicted racist Vicki Momberg was arrested in 2016 for using the K-word repeatedly, as she verbally abused police officers. JOHANNESBURG - Convicted racist, Vicki Momberg, is in police custody after handing herself over at the Douglasdale police station in Johannesburg.
Momberg handed herself over to the police, after consulting her legal team. WATCH: Where could convicted racist Vicki Momberg be? In August, she failed to hand herself in after her appeal against a crimen injuria conviction failed. READ: Vicki Momberg found guilty on four charges of crimen injuria Momberg was handed a two-year sentence after being found guilty of repeatedly using the k-word against a black police officer. Police will hand her over to prosecuting authorities at the Randburg Magistrate's Court.